Jug Island Trailhead 
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This hike was quite enjoyable! It’s considered a moderate to easy hike. We hiked for 2 hours and it was 5.5 km with 250m elevation. We loved the fresh air, tall trees, and pretty views. Save this hike trail for your next trip to Vancouver!

Kamayan Box from @buwan.toronto 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• Buwan is back and delicious as ever! They are located inside the Crave Food Hub as a take out spot. They serve their delicious silog, burgers, and even Kamayan box! We got their Kamayan box and it serves 4-6 people and it was absolutely delicious! It has their crispy pork, longanisa sausage, bbq chicken, shrimp, and grilled beef. All the meat is served on top of a bed of garlic fried rice. They also have some of their yummy house made sauce. Make sure you check this spot out at the Crave Food Hub.

We’re kicking of the holiday season with a giveaway from @heroburgersca ! We’re giving away 2 lucky winners a $30 gift card each! We love ordering our burgers through their app because we get loyalty points for each order, we can easily order ahead for pick up or delivery if we don’t feel like going out. Our favourite item here right now is their Smashed Burger with loads of Hero Certified Sauce!

Premium Wagyu Shabu Shabu from @ushi_shabu_shabu 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This is the newest hotpot spot to open up in Richmond Hill and we love it! They offer 3 different buffet menus. The main differences are in the quality and cut of meats. Choose from 1 of 3 buffet menus: Classic Beef, Premium Wagyu, and World Wagyu. The Premium Wagyu has Australian and USA Wagyu beef, while the World Wagyu set also includes Japanese Kobe Wagyu. We highly recommend the Premium Wagyu buffet because it was so delicious! You also get to select your broth. We chose the spicy miso and sukiyaki. The sukiyaki broth was so flavourful. We highly recommend this spot! From now till a Dec 16 enjoy 20% off AYCE and half off soup base.

Winter Carnival takes place from Dec 23 to Jan 8 at the Markham Fairgrounds. It is an indoor and outdoor event featuring Ice Sculptures, Mechanical Rides, Bouncy Castles, Games, Magicians, DJs, Food, Shopping, Animatronic Dinosaurs, and more! They have a variety of different wagyu grades including Japanese A5 Wagyu, Australian M7 Wagyu, US SRF Wagyu and more! The Deerioca Milk Tea Japanese Cheesecake, Cocoa S’more Latte & Marshmallow Matcha from @cheesegarden_ca x @thealley.ca 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• Cheese Garden and The Alley are debuting their collaboration dessert and drink for the holidays. This Deerioca Milk Tea Japanese Cheesecake has a milk tea cheesecake base, topped with a soft layer of cheese foam and deerioca tapioca. The S’more Latte & Marshmallow Matcha both have a tint of marshmallowness, which reminds us of the holidays. You can also try your luck by playing gara gara pon (lucky wheel) to win big or small prizes. Pre-orders for The Deerioca Milk Tea Japanese Cheesecake ($17.65) are now open! Pick up for the cake starts on Dec 10.

Chiushan Style Hotpot @oxclubto 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• We tried a new hotpot spot in Markham and quite enjoyed it. What really stood out at this hotpot restaurant was their delicious broth. They specialize in Chiushan style hot pot, so their broth does not have MSG and is not coated in oils. We quite enjoyed the variety of beef cuts they have at this restaurant. The best part about this hot pot is cooking the noodles at the very end and enjoying it with the hotpot broth! Because this soup base is not oily, you can enjoy the flavours of the soup with everything that you’ve cooked with the noodles. OX Club is celebrating their grand opening on Dec 9 to Dec 16. During this time period, every customer will get a plate of any Fresh Sliced Beef for only $1 with any soup base purchase at dinner time. You must be following @oxclubto to receive this promotion.

During the day this restaurant has a beautiful view of the harbour front, during the night you can see the CN Tower light up in the back. We visited XiaoLongKan Chinese Fondue in Richmond Hill and really enjoyed ourselves. They have special baskets to keep your jackets from smelling and aprons to keep your clothing clean. Gamja Tower & DIY Rice Balls from @hanyangjokbaltoronto 
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This is the most epic Gamjatang we’ve ever had and it was absolutely delicious! This dish is $19.99 per person and you must order a min of two orders. The soup itself was super flavourful with the perfect amount of spice. The meat on the pork bone was soft and fell right off the bone. The Gamjatang had lots of bean sprouts, veggies, a whole potato, rice cakes, mushrooms, sausages, and noodles. We also tried their DIY rice balls and love it! We didn’t realize how much we liked to play with our food. They also have a sweet and spicy house made soy with mustard paste that is absolutely amazing! We love this sauce and wish we can lather it on everything. Their Korean side dishes also on point! We will be back to have more!

All You Can Eat Authentic Turkish Breakfast form @meatpointca 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• We love the food at Meat Point, so we decided to try their All You Can Eat Authentic Turkish Breakfast. This Authentic Turkish Breakfast serves 2 people and costs $53.99. Each additional person is an additional $26.99 per person. This delicious breakfast includes the following dishes : Cheese Platter (Feta & Kashar), Olive Platter (Green & Black), Tomatoes and Cucumber, Cream Cheese, Pepper Paste, Butter, 2 Kinds of Jam, Honey, Nutella, Feta Cheese Rolls, Boiled Egg, Fries, and one hot platter of: Sucuklu Yumurta (Sujuk w/ Eggs) and Menemen (Shakshouka). The first servings of hot platters (sujuk w/eggs & shakshouka) are included in the breakfast. Any additional orders of the hot platters are extra charge, but everything else is all you can eat! Our favourite is the Sujuk with Eggs and the cheese platter! They serve this amazing breakfast everyday @meatpointca . Make sure you enjoy this deliciousness with some Turkish Tea.

Stone Pot Bowl and Spring Rolls from @linhanh.vietnamesecuisine 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This pho spot is quite tasty. The Stone Pot Bowl was so meaty! The portion was so big that we were able to share. There were 11 different types of meats you can choose from for AYCE: Beef Rump Cap, Striploin Steak, Beef Shish, Sucuk, Beef Parmesan Shish, Chicken Shish, Chicken Kebab, Chicken Wings, Lamb Shish, Lamb Legs, and Adana Kebab. Our favourite was the Striploin Steak and Chicken Shish. This was the first time we’ve had AYCE Turkish meats, so we quite enjoyed it.

Delicious Sri Lankan Food from @appas_original 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This spot in Markham serves some delicious Sri Lankan food. We’ve been here a few times before and every dish they have is full of flavour and spices. They are launching a new special dish: Palandi Kouttu Rotti, which features fried chicken and it is absolutely delicious! We love all their dishes that are wrapped in banana leaves because it brings our the aromatic flavours of the dish. The Chicken Devil Cheese Dosa and rolls were so tasty. It has the perfect amount of spiciness to it. This spot is a must try in Markham for amazing Sri Lankan dishes. You will find some classic dishes and some really unique dishes here, so there’s something tasty for everyone to eat.

Wings, Rolls, Bowls, and Poutines from @ohpapawings 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This new take out spot in Markham recently opened up and they serve up some tasty wings, rolls, bowls, and poutines. They have some tasty and unique wing flavours with some Sri Lankan spice. Their rolls and puff pastries are made in house and are absolutely delicious. We highly recommend the Chicken Keema and Butter Chicken Pastry. Their poutines are also on point! They have a Chilli Onion Poutine and it’s amazing! We’ve had Chilli Onion Fries and we’ve had poutine, but this combo is so tasty! They also have some party platters that you can order, which has a little bit of everything. We recommending calling ahead and ordering for pick up.

Congee, Rice Noodle Rolls, Claypot Rice & More from @westgateeats located inside @bigbeefbowl 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• We checked out the West Gate Classic Canton Eatery this weekend for located inside Big Beef Bowl. My parents actually love the menu here because it reminds them of home. They have classic canton dishes like rice noodles, congee, and claypot rice. They actually serve a dish called the West Gate Style Street Noodles, which is a dish my mom grew up eating in Guangzhou. It’s like a congee - noodle savoury dish that’s quite comforting. Our favourite dish was the Black Pepper Beef & Egg Claypot Rice. It’s a unique dish that we white enjoy. It even came with a soup to eat the crispy rice at the bottom of the Claypot! We quite enjoyed the food and recommend checking it out.

Rich Gyokai Tonkotsu Tsukemen, Spicy Tonkotsu Ramen, Gyzo, and Karaage from @ramen.raijin
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• We’ve heard great things about this ramen restaurant and were super impressed with how delicious the food was here! We absolutely loved the Tsukemen here. You can get the noodles served hot or cold. We opted for the hot option, but will be back to try the cold version next time. The thick noodles were nice and chewy. The ramen broth was rich and delicious. It was actually filled with lots of toppings and meat. The Spicy Tonkatsu ramen was the perfect amount of spice with a creamy flavourful broth. The chicken karaage and pork gyoza (they have veggie) were also tasty. The Kuromitsu Kinako Ice Cream and Matcha Pudding were fantastic, so make sure you save room for dessert!

Saku Sai Kai, Boat Noodles, Kanom Tuay, Kao Soi Soft Shell Crab & Pad Thai @eatbkkto 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• EAT BKK has some new menu items and we absolutely love it! During the weekends, they have a food cart set up at the front of the store. It really gave us some Thailand vacation vibes because the food was so authentic. The menu items from the cart are only available during the weekends. They have Saku Sai Kai (Chicken Stuffed Tapioca Pearls), Thai Boat Noodles, and Kanom Tuay (Steamed Coconut Pudding). We got all there items and they were very delicious. We also ordered their new Kao Soi Softshell Crab and classic Chicken & Shrimp Pad Thai. The food is delicious here and the portions are huge. Pair your food with some Unique Thai Cocktails like the Tipsy Thai Tea and Lycheetini. We really recommend checking out the rotational cart menu items!

••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• When food is served on skewers it always tastes better! This spot located inside the King Square Plaza is a AYCE hotpot spot. They serve some of their hotpot items on skewers, while some items are delivered by a cat robot! We got a triple soup base pot with spicy butter beef, spicy & sour, and mushroom soup base. The AYCE menu also comes with unlimited plum juice. You can also upgrade to the VIP or Diamond menu at an additional cost. The Diamond Menu allows you to order AYCE BBQ skewer items, signature dishes, snacks and desserts. If you don’t want to upgrade you can pay per order too, but it’s more worth it to just upgrade.

The Burger’s Priest only uses premium cuts of 100% Canadian Beef and the freshest ingredients to serve up a classic delicious burger. The best way to enjoy them is with their fresh-cut fries. Whenever we grab burgers, we have to get the milkshakes; it’s the perfect treat to finish your meal. We love pairing it with the Jinro Makgulli ! We also mixed it with Strawberry and Banana Milkis and it was AMAZING! It’s probably our new fav cocktail! They have some pretty good combo meals for 2-5 people under their “Deals” section. Our favourite wing flavour is their Honey Gar Par and Garlic Explosion. The wings were juicy, crispy and big! This take out spot is only 20 mins away for us in Ajax.

••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• Shudaxia Hotpot has a special AYCE promotion starting March 31 to April 2. During this special event, you can enjoy the regular hotpot AYCE menu, plus the a la carte items without additional charges. These a la carte items usually cost $5.99 to $25.99 each, but you can now order them as part of your AYCE menu. Our favourite a la carte dishes were the Shrimp Balls, Tai Chi Shrimp Paste, and Angus Beef Slices. We loved their “Hero’s 2 Flavour Pot in Pot” with Beef Bone Broth and Mushroom Broth. During this special event, Shudaxia will be giving away a VIP membership too. We totally recommend  checking this hotpot spot out. This promotion is totally worth it. Members will also receive $2 off!

We decided to check this spot out for dinner and loved it! We enjoyed the Chicken Schnitzel plate with Salad. Our favourite dish was the Burger Benny. They make their burger patties in house and you can really taste how delicious it is. We’ve never had anything like this before and it was amazing! It was served with a side of home fries. We got their Challah French Toast for dessert and topped it with strawberries, Nutella and maple syrup. It was totally bomb!

They specialize in non surgical solutions to all things cosmetic. It was my first time visiting a medical spa. I first had a consultation where my skin was analyzed, so they could choose the best treatment for my skin type. I had the 5D Collagen Light treatment where they stimulate cell growth and the production of collagen to tighten your skin and improve your skin appearance. I learned a lot about my skin and about skin health overall during my treatments. They offer lots of other services too.

They have a full bar loaded with drafts, frozen drinks, cocktails, and more! We were actually quite impressed with the food here. •••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• We love Ramona’s Kitchen, so we had to check out Ramona’s Cafe right next door. This cafe is super casual and cozy. They have a full brunch menu with sandwiches, Benny’s, dessert, coffees, smoothies, pastries and more! We absolutely love their Egg Benedicts. They have a few different options to choose from. We got the Salmon Benny, which was served on a croissant and the Avocado Bacon Benny, which was served on waffle. Our eggs were perfectly cooked to medium just the way we liked them. The BEST dish here is their Cookie Skillet. Fresh cookie dough baked on a skillet topped with ice cream. Legit the best thing EVER.

Their dinner menu has a little bit of everything and starts at 4 pm. They have some Indian dishes, Hakka dishes, Italian dishes, and American dishes. It’s a great spot to have dinner when you’re not quite sure what you’re in the mood for or when you’re with some friends who can’t decide where to eat. Johnny G’s also serves cocktails and spirits. Make sure you also save room and get the bread pudding. It is sooooo delicious! Check out Johnny G’s for some dinner.

Each brunch tower comes with a 3 tiered course and a hot or cold beverage of your choice. The first course is savoury and comes with: Kumato Caprese Salad, Egg Salad Cucumber Sandwich, Mushroom Truffle Danish. The second course features fresh biscuits: Honey Butter Biscuits, Blueberry Biscuits. The final course is sweets: Kalamansi Praline Choux Puff, Dear Hermes Verrine, Sparkling Wine w/ Rose Dacquois, and Fresh Fruits. Reservations are required to enjoy this afternoon tea (Minimum of 2 people required).

They smoke all their meats in house daily and they have have lots of different tasty sides. You can choose from jalapeño beans, coleslaw, barbecue beans, potato salads, Mac & Cheese and more! They have a pretty good selection of meats too including wings, ribs, turkey, chicken, brisket, pulled pork and more!

They come in 3 flavours: Pistachio, Tiramisu, and Matcha Yuzu! The Pistachio is filled with house made pistachio custard, topped off with white chocolate and pistachio crumbs. The Matcha Yuzu is filled with house made matcha and yuzu custard and topped off with white chocolate. The Tiramisu is filled with house made tiramisu and coffee custard, topped off with dark chocolate and icing sugar. The Tiramisu one is our absolute favourite!

You can choose from prints and patches to put on a sweater, t-shirt, hat, hoodie, or sweat pants. I designed a sweater with some patched and I love it! •••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This restaurant is located by Bokchon Hanok Village. This was one of the best meals I’ve had so far in Korea. There isn’t an English name for this restaurant, so you know it’s legit! I didn’t realize when I ordered that actually ordered 2 meals. It was really hot, so I wanted the cold buckwheat noodles and I wanted the shrimp tempura. The shrimp tempura was actually a meal set, which I also crushed. The noodles were sooooo delicious and so was the shrimp tempura. It only was $20 CAD for 2 whole meals!

•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• Visited this street vendor on a Sunday and there wasn’t any line. These pancakes are made fresh! You can choose your pancake filling. I got the vegetable, but there’s also sugar, cheese, or red bean. It costs about $1.50 to $3 Canadian depending on the filling you choose. This is a pretty tasty snack to fuel your shopping!

They’ve received this award every year since 2017 and they only have 4 items on the menu. I ordered all 4 items of course! I got the Chopped Noodles, Spicy Noodles, Dumplings, and Soybean Noodles. My favourite was the Chopped Noodled and Dumplings. The total of my bill was about $40 CAD. There’s usually huge line ups but we slipped right in and didn’t even have to wait! There’s actually 2 locations of this restaurant, which are 150m  by each other, so check the wait for both and go at off hours. We went at around 8 pm on a weekend.

It was quite the experience. Make sure bring cash only. I paid $9 CAD total here.

If you go after 7 pm then offer a 40% off discount because they close at 10 PM. I enjoyed an open air foot bath and relaxed some of the many relaxation rooms they had. I even made and cooked my own ramen! I ended my visit with some relaxation time on the massage chairs. They also offer full body scrubs and they have a bunch of different water baths, but you have to wear your birthday suit to enjoy those.

You choose your fresh seafood on the first floor of the market and they cook it for you upstairs. I had such a hard time choosing which restaurant because there are SO many! I ended up choosing the restaurant with the nicest old lady working. This place is like seafood heaven and totally worth checking out.

I sometimes splurge and get the instant ramen at the grocery stores in Markham, but it’s sooooo much better eating it in person! The ramen shop is 24 hours. I arrived at 11pm and still had to wait for a table. I got their Classic Tonkotsu Ramen, added extra noodles, egg, tea, and their vinegar sauce. I love that I get to customize my noodle texture and broth flavours. The best part is I get to eat quietly in a booth alone.

Ghibli Park in Japan! 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• Studio Ghibli makes some of my favourite animated films. This park recently opened up and continued to expand. It was difficult to get tickets and I had gotten them 3 months in advance! It was so nice to actually visit the park. There’s some sections where you cannot take photos or videos, so you’ll just have to visit in person! Be warned that there’s lots of lines for everything. It’s more of an “exhibit” located in a park rather than a theme park. They’ve only built phase 1, so we’ll be back in the future to see more.

I was lucky that I got into the Nintendo World section of the park early. The first thing I did was line up to get a ticket to eat at Kinopio’s Cafe. At 9:30 am we were able to get a ticket for 11:45 am, which us pretty awesome! Everything on the menu is super cute and it’s actually delicious! With all the food I ordered + 2 drinks it was about $75 CAD. Totally worth it!

They actually have several locations across the GTA and the Whitby one is about 20 mins from home. We tried a few of their menu items and quite enjoyed it. We loved their version of tacos. It was very unique and different from the traditional tacos. We also really enjoyed the burger because it was nice and juicy. Check out one of their locations across the GTA!

Shin-Yokohama Ramen Museum 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• I visited the Shin-Yokohama Ramen Museum. It’s about a 20 minute bullet train from Tokyo Station. You pay an admission fee to visit the museum. On the first floor you can learn about the history of ramen, create your own custom ramen,and shop. On the lower floors you can order and ear ramen from the different ramen shops. I ordered 3 bowls of small ramen for about $6.50 CAD each . I totally created my own ramen too!

Wagyu Roast Beef on Rice from @roastbeefohno
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This was the first time I’ve tried roast beef wagyu and it was simply amazing. I ordered the standard sized and it was so delicious. Half way through my meal I added extra meat. They have two kinds of sauce to choose from their Onion sauce or Wasabi sauce. I tried both and it was so yummy. I waited for about 45 minutes in line and my meal was under $25 CAD. I highly recommend eating here when visiting Japan. They do have a few locations so look for the one closest to you!

Premium Wagyu Shabu Shabu from @ushi_shabu_shabu
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This Shabu Shabu restaurant is the spot! They have 3 different tiers on their menu: The Classic, Premium Wagyu, and World Wagyu. They also have 7 different broths to choose from. We got the Premium Wagyu Tier with Spicy Miso and Sukiyaki. They currently have a FREE lobster limited time promotion on Mon-Thurs. When you pay with cash and you order  the Classic menu you get 1/2 a lobster for free, the Premium Wagyu menu you get 1 whole lobster for free, and the World Wagyu you get 1 whole lobster for free + 25% off! I we loved the quality of the meats and flavours of the broth here. It reminds us of the Shabu Shabu spot we visited in Japan.

Tum Thai, Tum Pholamai, Dad Diew, Pad Woonsen Cha-Om, Phad Gra Prao, Kor Moo Yang, and Tum Puu Plara from @somtumjinda
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This is the newest Michelin recommended Thai restaurant to open up in Toronto! Chef-owner Jinda’s specialty dishes are “Som Tum”, which means pounding with pestle to crush or break ingredients. This really brings out the flavours in all their dishes! We absolutely loved their papaya salads. We aren’t usually salad people, but the salads here are absolutely amazing. The dishes here are spicy and we are all for it because it compliments the flavours of the dishes. This restaurant is also really close to @plearncafeto , so you can actually order drinks & desserts from their menu too!

The minimum spend per booking is $500 and it costs $65/adult for 2 proteins. You can add additions proteins or upgrade for additions costs. You can find out more about their pricing at www.hibatchigta.com We set up our own tables, chairs, and cutlery and they Hibatchi chefs did the rest! They provided us salad, sake, steak, chicken, fried rice, entertainment and fun! The food was delicious, the sake was plentiful, and it was a lot of fun! We enjoyed our experience so much that we’ve teamed up with them to giveaway a $300 credit towards a Hibatchi party of your own! The winner must meet a minimum spend of $500 to book and redeem prize within 3 months.

They opened not too long ago and have some pretty yummy food and drinks. This is a great spot for Thai Tapas like their Grilled Pork, Chicken Tendons, Crispy Chicken Skin, and Mango Salad. Their mains are quite yummy too. Our favourite was the Seafood Bucket, Hunger Noodle, and Pineapple Fried Rice. •••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••Tengo KTV has a Happy Hour special!  Happy Hour is everyday from 3Pm-8PM. Happy Hours is only $13.99/person and each person gets a FREE drink! They also have some special cocktail drinks in a little convenient bag. They’re super unique and surprisingly delicious! All the ingredients you need to make your cocktail arrive in this little bag for you to mix and enjoy. They have 5 different flavours to choose from. We had a blast at Tengo KTV! Their KTV interface was super easy to use and they have SO MANY different songs in different languages. We sang lots of #kpop , oldies, plus the latest hits! We can’t wait to come back.

The food here is absolutely incredible! The Deep Fried Papaya Salad and Grilled Short Ribs were our favourite starters. We also got the Traditional Papaya Salad too. We ordered our favourite dish, the Shrimp Pad Thai. They use fresh noodles here just like in Thailand! We also tried something new, Duck Red Curry and Soft shell Crab Curry, which were both incredible. We got Pla Tod, the Fried Fish, which was huge and incredibly delicious. We finished off with Thai Iced Tea and a Mango Sticky Rice. We can’t wait to be back to try some of their other dishes!

Did you know the @tt_supermarket app has exclusive offers for members ?

We’ve used the T&T App for grocery deliveries and pick up orders, but we’ve recently found out that they have member only discounts at local restaurants! If you’re not a member already make sure to download the app and sign up to save. These discounts are a foodie lover’s dream! The discounts change on a weekly basis. Follow these easy steps to start saving:
1. Download the T&T App and open it 
2. Sign in or Sign Up
3. Click on T&T Rewards at the bottom 
4. Click on “Special Redemption” 
5. Browse through the different type of coupons you could redeem at local restaurants and shops
6. Be sure to check back regularly for new offers! 
We used the 50% off Pablo Cheese Tart coupon and enjoyed 50% off our entire order. We clicked “Claim This Offer” at the shop and showed the cashier. It was super easy to use!

Halloween Haunt Sept 22 to Oct 29 on Select Nights  @canadaswonderland 
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••Fall is here and so is Halloween Haunt at Canada’s Wonderland! Immerse yourself in the spirit of Halloween, nightmare, screams, and Haunt!  Explore seven spooky mazes, terrifying scare zones,
hundreds of monsters, thrilling night rides, spooktacular food and awesome live entertainment. You can get unlimited visits with a Canada’s Wonderland Gold Pass for the remainder of 2023 and all of 2024. We totally recommend purchasing the Fright & Fast Lane Plus Passes to bypass lines at certain attractions. It’s so worth it. For those who want to come to Haunt but are afraid of the monsters, you can purchase a “no boo necklace” throughout the park. These necklaces let the monsters know to keep a little extra distance. Our favourite part of our visit is all the Halloween themed food and to see the park with so many lights at night time. Check out Halloween Haunt on select nights at Canada’s Wonderland till Oct 29. Visit their website for details.

Pho Lobster, Pho Bat Da, Boneless Chicken Feet Salad, and Spring Rolls from @phongondatviet 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This is the best Pho restaurant in Thornhill. All the food here is legit delicious! They serve a tasty Pho Lobster. They use a whole Fresh Live Nova Scotia Lobster and have limited quantities daily. In the Pho Lobster there is also 2 bone in beef ribs, lots of beef, beef balls, and noodles. You can actually taste the lobster flavours in the pho broth and it’s was absolutely amazing. The lobster was nice and meaty too. They also have their tasty Pho Bat Da served in a hot stone bowl. The broth was nice and beefy, the way we liked it. This dish has beef balls, rare beef, bone in beef rib, tendon, tripe, brisket and crunchy flank. We love the stone bowls because it keeps our pho hot while we take photos. The quality, quantity, flavours and presentation of all the food here is spot on. We highly recommend checking out this pho spot.

They’re a donut shop located in Kensington Market on Baldwin Street. We always get a donut here whenever we’re in Kensington. We got a half dozen this time with the following flavours:
- Vegan Sprinkled Donut
- Cookies and Cream 
- Spicy Mango Pineapple Fritter 
- OG Vanilla Bean 
- Brown Butter Sea Salt 
The donuts here are super fluffy and we love the flavours. Our favourite was the Brown Butter Sea Salt and Cookies & Cream. We highly recommend this donut shop. They actually offer delivery to the GTA (Yes a Markham too) and they’re on Skip The Dishes and Uber Eats.

Charidise recently renovated and they are located on the second floor of 27 Baldwin Street. They also have a lovely patio in the front where we enjoyed some alcoholic beverages and snacks. - Sausage Minced Pork Rice
- Traditional Fish Cake 
- Taiwanese Beef Noodle Soup
- Takoyaki
- Popcorn Chicken 
- Iced Charidise Milk Tea w/Pearl
- Royal Hawaiian 
- Lychee Lime Mint Sparkling
- Garden City 
- Teriyaki Salmon Appetizer
- Spicy Chicken Wonton

The food and drinks were so yummy here. Our favourite was the Beef Noodle Soup, Popcorn Chicken and Royal Hawaiian. We can’t wait for Taisho to open up!

- Aburi Salmon Pressed Sushi
- Tenderloin Sizzling Steak 
- Grilled Miso Salmon Caesar Salad

Everything was so fresh and tasty here! They also have a daily special menu with some chef special recommended dishes. Make sure you save room for dessert because it’s amazing!

@ebisuonrobson has some of the freshest sushi in Vancouver 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• Ebisu on Robson is one of our favourite spots for fresh sushi in Vancouver. The tuna sashimi is absolutely incredible here. It’s on par with when we had it at the dish markets in Japan. They have a wide range of sashimi, sushi rolls, Japanese dishes, cocktails and more!
Here are some of the things we ordered:
- Salmon Carpaccio 
- Truffle Fries 
- Salmon Pepper Popper 
- Volcano Roll 
- Philadelphia Roll
- BBQ Wagyu Beef 
- Mentaiko Yakiudon

Salted Egg Yolk Ice Cream Cake from @vavadesignercakes 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This is VaVa’s First Ice Cream Cake! It is a limited edition Salted Egg Yolk Ice Cream Cake. The Salted Egg Yolk Ice Cream Cake was just launched right before this year’s Mid- Autumn Festival (the second most significant celebration in China after the Chinese New Year). Our parents just came back from vacation so we celebrated Mid-Autumn festival with this smooth salted egg yolk ice cream cake. The cake had a rich salted egg yolk sauce, handmade chocolate decorations (in the shape of a moon), silky coconut frosting, and a cookie base. This ice cream cake is super unique! We’ve never had anything like it.

You can add noodle, cheese, rice cake, rice, and stir fried rice (after) to your braised chicken dish. - Adana Ali Nazik
- Sac Tava 
- Spinach & Cheese Pide 
- Lahmacun 
- Dessert: Kunefe, Sutlac, & Baklava 
- Turkish Tea

They are there from Tuesdays to Saturday from 12pm to 8pm (or until sold out). Everything on their menu is absolutely incredible. They have the best Oxtail Burger we’ve ever had. You’ve got to check this spot out!

@vietnoms.toronto just opened a new location in Thornhill 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• Vietnoms’ original location is at 243 Sheppard Ave East in North York. They opened up a second location at 7000 Bathurst St in Thornhill. Vietnoms specializes in Vietnamese pho, street food, and drinks. The drinks on their menu are so good! The Matcha Lemonade is a must order. We also tried two of their popular dishes from the Off Menu Specials and loved it! We got their Sizzling Beef, Egg & Meatball served with a baguette and loved the flavours and sauciness. The Crab & Pork Tapioca Noodle Soup was full of crab flavour and the tapioca noodles were nice and bouncy. We love that their newer location is closer to us. Here’s everything we ate:
- Matcha Lemonade 
- Espresso Tonic 
- Vietnamese Beef Carpaccio 
- Chicken & Shrimp Spring Rolls 
- Crab & Pork Tapioca Noodle Soup 
- Sizzling Beef, Egg & Meatball

Bowls, Burgers, Poutines, French Tacos, Baguettes, and Pitas from @torino.ca 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• Torino is a famous halal restaurant in Montreal that’s now open in Toronto! They have 26 branches in total and 2 of them are in Toronto. We visited the one located in @thejunctionfoodco and quite enjoyed the food. Both locations in Toronto are located in a ghost kitchen, so it’s take out only. You can order for delivery or pick up. All their food is made to order using fresh ingredients and house made sauce. You can choose any kind of meat or toppings to add to your Bowls, Burgers, Poutines, French Tacos, Baguettes, and Pitas. Here’s what we got:
- Mini Shrimp Bowl with Red Rice 
- Piri-Piri Chicken Strips French Taco with Garlic Potatoes 
- Beef Tenderloin Poutine (made with garlic potatoes)
- Merguez (beef sausage) Baguette 
- Beef Burger 
- Beef Tenderloin Pita with French Fries 
Our favourite dish was the Piri-Piri Chicken Strips French Taco with Garlic Potatoes and Beef Tenderloin Poutine that was made with Garlic Potatoes. Their Garlic Potatoes is so unique and delicious. Check out one of their 26 locations.

••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••Taisho is newest Japanese Grill Restaurant to open up in Toronto. They are located at the first floor of Charidise on Baldwin Street. They have an All You Can Eat menu for lunch and dinner. Plus you can order alcoholic beverages, cocktails, coffee, bubble tea and other drinks at an additional cost. Their AYCE menu has lots of different high quality meats you can order to grill. They also have antipasto dishes, rice, noodle, Hawaiian poke bowl, sushi hand rolls and dessert too!

Tasty Vietnamese Food in Richmond Hill @phohungphat 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• We visited a Vietnamese restaurant located in Richmond Hill for the first time last week and quite enjoyed it! The food here is delicious and the price is super fair. Here’s what we ordered:
- Deep Fried Chicken Wings with Fish Sauce 
- Fine Rice Vermicelli Grilled Pork, Grilled Chicken, & Grilled Shrimp on Sugar Cane 
- Beef on Steamed Rice 
- Beef Rib Rice Noodle Soup in Stone Bowl 
We highly recommend the Fine Rice Vermicelli Grilled Pork, Grilled Chicken, & Grilled Shrimp on Sugar Cane. It’s basically building your own rolls and we loved it! The Beef Rib Rice Noodle Soup in Stone Bowl was really yummy too! Check out this hidden gem tucked away in Richmond Hill!

Indoor Golf, Nintendo Switch, Karaoke, & delicious food @thegolfloungeca @maizonkitchen
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• The Golf Lounge is a newly renovated indoor golf lounge located in Richmond Hill. You can practice your golf swing and play indoor golf games. In addition to indoor golf they also have Nintendo Switch, Karaoke, darts, and more! They have open bays, private rooms, and a big space for parties! They have a lovely bar and they’ve actually collaborated with some neighbour restaurants to bring you delicious food! You can enjoy delicious food from @ryu_izakaya , @jokers905club , and @pizzaiologourmetpizza and play indoor golf at the same time. We had a BLAST here and really enjoyed the food with some beers. The best part was their auto tee up system, so we didn’t have to break our backs. It was the perfect spot to hang out with some friends. We highly recommend making a reservation by calling.

@mrpuffs_markhamroad is now open! 
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• Mr. Puffs on Markham Road is now open! They are actually the closest one to us in Markham. They sit basically on the board of Scarborough and Markham. This was the first time we’ve ever had Mr. Puffs and it’s worth all the hype. You can these Puffs in 12, 30, 50, 65, 130, and even in a Boquet! You can choose fr over 30 different glazes for your Puffs. You can also get Puffs with ice cream too called Mount Olympus. They have milkshakes, coffees, and tea too. The prices are super reasonable and the Puffs are so delicious. Here’s what we got:
- 30 Puffs - Cookies & Cream and Biscoff Glaze 
- Choco-Bueno Mount Olympus 
- Iced Coffee with Pumpkin Sweet Foam 
- Lotus Biscoff Latte
We highly recommend checking out Mr. Puffs on Markham Road.

They use fresh ingredients and make all their sauces in house. They have burritos, bowls, tacos, quesadillas, nachos, fried and more! They have quite a few different protein options you can choose from and combine like chicken, steak, ground beef, shrimp, halibut, soya, and more. Here’s what we got:
- Halibut & Shrimp Bowl 
- Steak Tacos 
- BBQ Chicken Burrito 
- BBQ Steak Quesadilla 
- Beef Nachos 
- Churros 
Our favourite was the BBQ Steak Quesadilla and Halibut & Shrimp Bowl. We highly recommend getting their burrito sauce and hot sauce. It goes so well with their food.

They specialize in Korean street foods like Tteokbokki, Kimbap, rice bowls, udon, and fried fish cakes. We got their Combo for Three which includes: 2 Tteokbokki, Basket of Deep fried snacks, 2 pops and 1 Kimbap. We highly recommend getting their Rose Tteokbokki and adding cheese. It is absolutely divine, but honestly the Creamy Carbonara Tteokbokki was amazing too. From Nov 11 to Nov 30 they have a dine in promotion!  All you have to do is f ollow @sinjeon_uptown_toronto and if you spend $30 or more(before tax) you get korean drinks (Milkis or Banana milk). If you spend $45 or more(before tax), you get free spam mayo rice bowl. This spot is totally worth checking out. We highly recommend this for all Tteokbokki lovers.

Hotpot @xiaolongkantoronto 
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• Hotpot season is our favourite season and it’s totally here! We enjoyed some very tasty hotpot at XiaoLongKan. When you walk into the restaurant it feels like you’re transported into China. We got 3 different soup bases: Sukiyaki, Traditional Spicy, & Wild Mushroom Soup. Our favourite soup base was the Wild Mushroom! It really brought out the flavours of the food we were eating. Here’s some of the things we ordered: 
- Angus Beef Roll 
- Chicken Roll
- Sliced Fish Fillet
- Shrimp Paste
- Vegetables Platter 
- Udon
- Tofu
- Luncheon Meat 
- Brown Sugar Rice Cake 
- Milk Roll 
We love the variety of different hotpot items you can order. Their hotpot dishes are fresh and good quality. The Angus Beef Rolls and Shrimp Paste were our absolute favourite dishes. This restaurant is pretty big and opened till 3 am, so it’s the perfect spot for late night eats with friends. They currently have an in store promotion: Spend $150 and receive a $30 coupon which is redeemable on your next purchase of $100 or more.

Turkish Dinner @meatpointca 
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• Meat Point is one of our go to Turkish Restaurants because the food is consistently delicious. This was actually one of the first Turkish restaurants we first started to eat at where we fell in love with the cuisine. Whether you’re there for breakfast, lunch or dinner their food always hits the spot. We went for a date night this weekend and here’s what we got:
- Paca Soup & Lentil Soup
- Shepard Salad 
- Mixed Dip Platter: Haydari, Antep Ezme, Hummus & Eggplant Ezme
- Pasha Sultan Mix Platter: Adana Kebap (1 skw), Chicken Shish (1 skw), Meat Shish (1 skw), Chicken Wings (2 pcs), Meat and Chicken Doner served with grilled tomatoes + pepper, white & bulgur rice + freshly baked pita bread
- Chicken Guvec (Stew) 
- Vegan Pide 
- Baklava
- Turkish Tea 
We love their Special Mixed Platters because you get to eat a little bit of everything. All their skewers and meats are cooked to absolute perfection. We highly recommend this spot for date night or with a big group of friends. Bookmark this spot or save this reel for your next night out.

Winterfest is back @canadaswonderland from Nov 17 to January 6 on select nights 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• We love Winterfest at Canada’s Wonderland because the whole park transforms into a magical winter wonderland filled with Holiday Spirit and cheer! It’s such an immersive experience filled with food, drinks, and activities for everyone! We enjoyed ice skating, love entertainment, photos with Santa, musical performances, holiday themed food & drinks, and more! We really enjoyed some of the holiday themed food and drinks. Here what we tried:
- Funnel Cakes: Gingerbread & Strawberry
- Cocktails: Midwinter Sprite Spritz, Northern Lights, & Egg Nog 
- Food: Turkey Dinner Ball, Cured Smoked Beef Brisket, Loaded Smash Potato Seafood Chowder & Beef Stew, Comet’s Holiday Mac n’ Cheese, & Deep Fried Red Velvet Oreos 
We honestly love Winterfest at Canada’s Wonderland and it’s one of our favourite activities we look forward to during then holiday season.

- French Onion Soup
- Butter Chicken Mac & Cheese 
- 2 LBS of Wings (Hot Honey & Honey Mustard)

On Monday they have half price wings, Tuesday & Wednesday they have Trivia Night & $20 Wing + Beer combo on Game Nights. We totally recommend checking out this spot for good food & a great time.

•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This small sushi restaurant in Richmond Hill is serving up some all you can eat sushi. Their sushi menu is unique. Before you can order AYCE, you must finish the first 2 rounds of food that the chef serves you. The first round includes: miso soup, salad, & edamame beans. The second round includes Chef’s choice of: 18 pcs of Sashimi, 8 pcs sushi, and 1 maki roll. Once you’ve eaten the two rounds you can order anything you’d like from the AYCE menu. It’s such a unique way of dinning because the chef’s choices set will change. This lets you get to try something different & new before you dive into your favourites!

We had some unique Turkish dishes that we really enjoyed and haven’t had anywhere else. The most delicious dishes we had were the Chicken Steak, Mozzarella Pide with Chicken Doner & the Sutlac. The Chicken steak was cooked to perfection & the Pide was so flavourful. The Sutlac was tje west we’ve had with the perfect amount of sweet. Here’s everything we ate:
- Mixed Dip Appetizer & Fresh Turkish Bread 
- Greek Salad 
- Lentil Soup 
- Chicken Steak 
- Grilled Meat Balls 
- Mozzarella Pide with Chicken Doner 
- Turkish Tea 
- Dessert: Sutlac, Trileche, & Kunefe
We highly recommend checking out this spot. Bookmark this for where you’re near Mississauga.

Hong Kong x Thai Fusion food @grandpathaitoronto 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• Grandpa Thai in North York is a Hong Kong & Thai Food Fusion cafe. We love the flavours and spices on these fusion dishes. Here’s what we got:
- Chicken Pad Thai 
- Coconut Latte 
- House Special Cafe Pho
- Deep Fried Chicken Wings - Tom Yum Kung Flavour
- Deep Fried Seafood Rice Net Spring Roll 
- Baked Thai Red Curry Fries
- Tom Yum Kung Seafood Risotto with Cheese 
- Caramel Cookie Milky Cream French Toast 
We absolutely loved the Tom Yum Kung Seafood Risotto with Cheese. It was loaded with seafood and cheesy goodness. The chicken wings with Tom Yum Kung flavour were super crispy and tasty. We highly recommend their coffee drinks with their sweet tasty toasts. Check out this unique fusion cafe!

Signature Chicken Wings & Delicious Eats @momspanfriedbun 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• Mom’s Pan Fried Buns has some tasty Fried Chicken Wings at an affordable price. They have 8 Signature flavours to choose from and 6 pieces is only $6.99. Their flavours include: Sprinkle Cheese, Onion Cheese, Honey Mustard, Honey Garlic, Cumin, Plum, Spicy & Sweet Chilli. In addition to their tasty wings, they also have a variety of different dishes like Pan Fried Buns, Dumplings, Noodles, Congee, Wontons, and more! We visited the downtown location for the first time and had a wonderful experience. The staff were very knowledgeable and friendly. They had some really good recommendations. Here’s what we ate:
- Sprinkle Cheese, Onion Cheese, & Spicy Fried Chicken Wings 
- Savoury & Juicy Pan Fried Pork Bun 
- Spicy & Sour Glass Noodle Soup with Tofu Pudding 
- Braised Tofu in Master Sauce 
- Chinese Scallion Pancake 
- Pan Fried Pork Dumpling
- Traditional Pumpkin Cake 
- Beef Pie
The food is absolutely delicious here. We loved the crispy chicken wings & tasty pan fried buns. We love that they have two locations: Toronto & Markham. We totally recommend checking them out.

They have 6 different signature noodles with your choice of type of noodle. We highly recommend getting their rice noodles. We absolutely love the noodle soup here. - Signature Beef Noodle Soup 
- Beef Brisket & Beef Noodle Soup
- Fried Brown Sugar Mochi

••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• We had brunch at A Corner Cafe in North York on Christmas Day and loved it! They have some new brunch menu items! Here’s what we got:
- Hot & Cold Vietnamese Latte
- Smoked Salmon Egg Benny
- Fried Chicken Egg Benny 
- French Toast 
The Fried Chicken Benny & French Toast are must order items. The Fried Chicken was super tasty and not dry at all. The French Toast was incredible! We absolutely loved that it was served with Kawartha Blackberry Thunder Ice Cream. If you’re looking for a tasty brunch check out A Corner Cafe in North York!

•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• We quite enjoyed the pho here. The broth is flavourful and clean plus they have thick cut brisket & quality rare beef. We love that they have combos here, so you can get a noodle + a small appetizer as a combo. We really liked the chicken wings here too cause they were crispy and full of fish sauce flavour. We also tried the crispy wonton with pork and shrimp. We totally recommend checking this spot out! There is a bit of a wait and they currently don’t offer take out.

@bingz_canada just got some new menu items! 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••We love Bingz because it’s delicious cheap eats. They recently got some new menu items like the Sichuan Sesame Sauce Shrimp Wontons & Smoking Hot Golden Nuggets. Their Golden Nuggets are now bigger, juicer & more tender than before. They also have a Spicy BBQ sauce you must get to dip them in too! They also updated their Signature Beef Crispy Burger. The new signature beef is still slow cooked and full of flavours, but the meat is now more lean and the crispy burger has a bigger portion of meat. Their brand is from Hanoi Vietnam and they have over 80 locations across Vietnam, Korea and Malaysia. We’re super excited that they’re finally in Toronto! When you walk into the cafe it feels like you’ve been transported into Vietnam! We love the decor, uniform & vibes of this coffee shop. We tried some of their coffee and absolutely loved it! We highly recommend their White (Bac Xic) Coffee and Coconut Green Rice Smoothie. They’ve got lots of other unique drinks & banh mi that we’ll have to come back for.

@thebigcasserole is new restaurant that opened up in Richmond Hill
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• This restaurant specializes in chicken soup hotpot, claypot rice, handmade dim sum and sizzling casseroles. We tried their claypot rice, dumplings and noodle soup. Here’s what we got: 
- Classic Sausage & Dried Pork Claypot Rice + Salted Egg
- Seasoned Beef with Egg Claypot Rice 
- Mushroom Bamboo Chicken Soup with Vermicelli 
- House Chicken Soup Wonton

New Japanese Bakery just opened Downtown Toronto @hitotoki_bakery
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• You know we love all things Japanese, so we had to check out this bakery downtown. They specialize in Shokupan, Tarts & Palmier. All their baked goods are baked fresh daily. You can really taste the freshness when you bite into the flakes tarts.  Their official grand opening is on Jan 26th. To celebrate their Grand Opening, from Jan 26 – Jan 27 the first 20 customers each day can each receive one free box of 4 tarts (included flavours: original, strawberry, crème brule, tangerine). The first 40 customers each day can also enjoy Buy one get one FREE for their tarts only (max purchase of 4 tarts/pp). We loved their flakey tarts! They’re filled with delicious cream & topped with fruit. We highly recommend the Creme Brulee Almond Tart.
